RUNNING DOXYGEN with graphviz (which shows graph dependencies visually) 

cd into the Doxygen_Setup folder of root catkin_ws
$ doxygen Doxygen_Setup

Install Graphviz:

For Ubuntu 12.04: 

$ sudo apt-add-repository ppa:dperry/ppa-graphviz-test # --> this may or may not prove necessary

$ sudo apt-get update
$ sudo apt-get autoremove graphviz
$ sudo apt-get install graphviz

If you get this error "graphviz : Depends: libgraphviz4 (>= 2.18) but it is not going to be installed", run the following

$ sudo apt-get remove libcdt4
$ sudo apt-get remove libpathplan4
$ sudo apt-get install graphviz

